So, as we become to use single-filters more and more, we need to extend our ITs to load few modules from config files and execute such few modules(check(s) + filters) on file.
I do not want to do this in this PR, as it will extend scope of fix a lot and delay functional fix. It is better to do this as separate issue - #7546 .

One issue with the entire config is it may produce similar violations from different checks. IMO, that might be better to show.

you might talk about CI verification item that run whole config over file,
for this particular CI, I need Input that have no violations. So I used newly created file as some "prove" that suppression actually works.
